# Streamerbot_SelfHosted_Chat
Streamerbot SelfHosted Chat

This is a self hosted chat that utilizes Streamerbot to write all the chat messages into a text file, read them and create a webpage using node.js

Current chat functions:
--Download twitch users emote.
--Display user PointSystem current Ranking.
--Automatic fetch your Twitchsubs.
--Assign custom medals for the chatter, automatic assign submedal for twitch.
--Chatter can change the color of the chat and text as they wish.
--Display wich platform the user is current in.

We have the txt files:
ChatLastline: counts the amount of messages send.
ChatOverlay: save all the messages.
memberlistYoutube: save the members, so you can use for effects and etc.
ignoredList: list of users to be ignored.
userAddonList: where we save all users addons, like chat and text colors.
twitchSubscribers: fetched using twitch API. YOU MUST REPLACE YOUR CREDENTIALS AT THE SERVER.JS TO WORK
DownloadAllTwitchEmotes: List of emotes to replace for twitch chatters.
ChatSVGAddonList: List of SVG icons to use in the chat.

HOW TO INSTALL:

run the following comands using cmd at the chat folder:
npm init -y
npm install express fs path axios cheerio puppeteer


Then run the start_server.bat or open a cmd and run server.js to start the server.
Use the link: http://localhost:3000/index.html as a browser source.

Obs: 
To rank the users we're using the PointSystem, and RankingSystem with smallchanges from Streamerbot Extensions:
https://extensions.streamer.bot/docs?topic=49
https://extensions.streamer.bot/docs?topic=223
Also the chat layout is based of StreamElements chat.
